webpackJsonp([0xeda4409a0d7f],{738:function(A,a){A.exports={data:{post:{id:"/home/travis/build/h0ssimo/beta/content/posts/portfolio/2018-07-01--Minotaur-Action-Figure/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<h2>The Minotaur Action Figure<br /></h2>\n<p>I tried a couple of cool techniques on this one. I created it to try to show the mood better, and also to improve my skill set. I developed my own workflow for such works during this fun project; which I’m gonna talk about.</p>\n\n  <a class="gatsby-resp-image-link" href="/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_01_square-d8badd254ee389331bbaf463628c112b-222c6.jpg" style="display: block" target="_blank" rel="noopener">\n  \n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;" alt="minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_01_square" title="" src="/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_01_square-d8badd254ee389331bbaf463628c112b-78f2b.jpg" srcset="/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_01_square-d8badd254ee389331bbaf463628c112b-dce19.jpg 200w,\n/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_01_square-d8badd254ee389331bbaf463628c112b-c1413.jpg 400w,\n/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_01_square-d8badd254ee389331bbaf463628c112b-78f2b.jpg 800w,\n/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_01_square-d8badd254ee389331bbaf463628c112b-222c6.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n<h3>Sculpting and Posing Process<br /></h3>\n<p>I already had the basic <a href="/portfolio/Minotaur/">A-Pose</a> done, so all I had to do was to pose him, without losing my already sculpted details. <br /></p>\n<p>For such complicated poses, I find it hard to try using zbrush’s Transpose Master. So I sent my low res mesh to Maya, rigged it -since I’m comfortable with rigging in Maya- and then posed it. I brought back my character into zbrush, and projected all the details back to my mesh using Displacement maps and continued sculpting some pose-related details and volumes.<br />\n<br />\n\n  <a class="gatsby-resp-image-link" href="/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_02_square-79abcffc5e0982842df19cf40665155e-222c6.jpg" style="display: block" target="_blank" rel="noopener">\n  \n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;" alt="minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_02_square" title="" src="/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_02_square-79abcffc5e0982842df19cf40665155e-78f2b.jpg" srcset="/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_02_square-79abcffc5e0982842df19cf40665155e-dce19.jpg 200w,\n/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_02_square-79abcffc5e0982842df19cf40665155e-c1413.jpg 400w,\n/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_02_square-79abcffc5e0982842df19cf40665155e-78f2b.jpg 800w,\n/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_02_square-79abcffc5e0982842df19cf40665155e-222c6.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Also, I changed some of my artistic decisions along the way, in comparison to what I had originally.<br /></p>\n<p>I used SnakeHook and Slash2 brushes to sculpt the cloth details.<br /></p>\n<p>I rendered it using ZBrush. Just created a couple of renderpasses and composed them in Photoshop.<br />\n<br />\n\n  <a class="gatsby-resp-image-link" href="/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_03_square-627627b47edae51c39993da5cfc4314e-222c6.jpg" style="display: block" target="_blank" rel="noopener">\n  \n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;" alt="minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_03_square" title="" src="/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_03_square-627627b47edae51c39993da5cfc4314e-78f2b.jpg" srcset="/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_03_square-627627b47edae51c39993da5cfc4314e-dce19.jpg 200w,\n/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_03_square-627627b47edae51c39993da5cfc4314e-c1413.jpg 400w,\n/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_03_square-627627b47edae51c39993da5cfc4314e-78f2b.jpg 800w,\n/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_03_square-627627b47edae51c39993da5cfc4314e-222c6.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3>Inspiration<br /></h3>\n<p>I kinda get bored quickly, so I need to improve in a daily manner. So I asked a friend of mine, Ardalan Hashemi Asl, who is a capable 2D artist, how to level up my works. <br />\nWe came to the conclusion that if I needed to level up, I needed to leave my comfort zone in order to push my limits. So I decided to create a posed version of my character as if it’s going to be sold as a premium action figure by some toy company.<br /></p>\n<p>I hope these kinda thoughts and works, inspire you guys as well.</p>\n<p>For higher resolution images, please visit my Artstation.</p>',fields:{slug:"/Minotaur-Action-Figure/",prefix:"portfolio/2018-07-01"},frontmatter:{title:"The Minotaur Action Figure",author:"Hossein Moayed",category:"portfolio",date:"2018-07-01T00:00:00.000Z",cover:{childImageSharp:{resize:{src:"/static/minotaur_statue_by_hossimo_04_square-f6fb651480d01c121837f4739c6f3613-ada8c.jpg"}}}}},authornote:{id:"/home/travis/build/h0ssimo/beta/content/parts/author.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>To make it short, I’m a 3D Character Artist experienced in character pipelines for both animations and games.</p>"},site:{siteMetadata:{facebook:{appId:"298710090861252"}}}},pathContext:{slug:"/Minotaur-Action-Figure/",prev:{id:"/home/travis/build/h0ssimo/beta/content/posts/portfolio/2018-06-11--Minotaur/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",fields:{slug:"/Minotaur/",prefix:"portfolio/2018-06-11"},frontmatter:{title:"The Minotaur",category:"portfolio",tags:["fantasy","sculpture"],date:"2018-06-11T00:00:00.000Z"}},next:{id:"/home/travis/build/h0ssimo/beta/content/posts/portfolio/2018-07-07--Sweet-and-Delicate/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",fields:{slug:"/Sweet-and-Delicate/",prefix:"portfolio/2018-07-07"},frontmatter:{title:"Sweet And Delicate",category:"portfolio",tags:["realistic","sculpture"],date:"2018-07-07T00:00:00.000Z"}}}}}});
